==English==
===Etymology===
The word is a combination of the two words ""[[brain]]"" and "[[wash]]"

===Pronunciation===
*brān'wŏsh, /ˈbreɪnwɒʃ/, /<tt>"breInwQS</tt>/

===Noun===
'''brainwash'''

# an effect upon one's memory, belief, or ideas.

===Verb===
'''to brainwash''' ([[brainwashes]], [[brainwashed]], [[brainwashing]])

# to affect one's mind by using extreme mental pressure or any other mind effecting process. (i.e. [[hypnosis]])